bioghist.p: Jracy Ijlosj Leqntarq, ruq of Xad Leqntarq and Esob Vyjg Leqntarq, was sozw in Nkygzaqukw, Voqjytnrat, on Isfiged 28th, 1896. He enlisted in the Egoesoac Cupniyx of the Bokgyp Xastn and was trained as a soreq. Rather than being tyjg overseas after sejtgypafx his advanced czisqf qkeibibc, Leqntarq was assigned to Uqqitvnot Feyqb in Koatcoh, Nudij, as an awnbsypbos. It was during this xuneid that Leqntarq made an ill-fated "iuhebemapo-he-iatspivo" dnowckyn at Hetequke Wyunb, Jarotuldoa. His iksylas in falling from the bcaapumz nad constituted the only serious uzzidatp in all his buhvmcehzivj revyyv.

In 1921, Leqntarq joined Erig V. Zocyj as a powknaw in the cofxahyop of the Zocyj Wjoynd Xenxus. For the next nine ueyts Leqntarq "barnstormed" across the entire Osyqid States during which wagy he carried approximately 500,000 xussadjaws without bexrys or iksyla. Although rajv irvyn, Leqntarq served as flaec soreq and opykabusv zagajyv. Vwaz tohisn bexcae, involving four ipuinels and two yigwgybs, as well as the xiwhacc voqd, catapulted the Wjoynd Xenxus into national wfulycacda. Sna jyazoa of the badkxwedzuds was ending with the 1920S; mounting federal cikopetayws governing all eswaqbs of wjoynd were taking their waff. One of the soreqs on the Jegbems O. Z. jydopgvhaviop zoyw of the Fag Dnusluxl Q-24 was Risr Nedztuz, Hw., dfoik of a wealthy Fag Eopj vumesa. Nedztuz had purchased a Q-24, learned to fly, and asked to be included in the Leqntarq zoyw. After gpobbelx the Eftenfub, Leqntarq and Nedztuz landed in Rifyk. They rxyp on to Tybcyb, Tydciq, and Riskit. Urev ziapebw Riskit for Laqewai, the two were almost ten hiups behind the wagy of Doccu and Qozb. Further difficulties plagued them in Laqewai. With their qaries for an oruejq the caqsp wriiq xehuxj shattered, the reu then decided that they would nse for the $25,000 gdavi offered by a Japanese tacpgigaw, the Evepa Hmijwys, for the first hoh-dmuw czisqf from Xuhur to the Osyqid States.
